SIMPLE: inharmonious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inharmonious
<hw>In`har*mo"ni*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>harmonious</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>inharmonieux</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not harmonious; unmusical; discordant;
dissonant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sounds <qex>inharmonious</qex> in themselves and harsh.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Conflicting; jarring; not in harmony.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inharmoniously</ent>⟦br⟧
